modules.description: This module implements the Blake2b cryptographic hashing algorithm, supporting incremental updates and direct hashing. It operates on byte sequences (`Stdlib.Bytes.t`) and produces fixed-size hash outputs. Use it to generate secure hashes for data integrity verification, digital signatures, or content-addressed storage systems.

This module provides the Blake2b cryptographic hashing algorithm, enabling both incremental hash updates and direct hashing of byte sequences. It supports operations for initializing, updating, and finalizing hash computations, producing fixed-size 64-byte outputs. Use it to verify data integrity, generate content identifiers, or create secure digital signatures for arbitrary binary data. Example: compute a hash from a file's contents or stream data incrementally to build a hash over multiple buffers.
